# Collaborative documents (shared-document)

> Merit-based collaborative editing: official block text, proposed variants, voting with заслуги, manual vs auto apply. Canonical product/architecture: `docs/prd/shared-document/business-approved-tz.md`; PRD folder: `docs/prd/shared-document/`.

---

## Concept

- **Document** (`documents` collection): belongs to a **community** (`communityId`). Types: `imageOfFuture` (one per community — ОБ), `description` (one per project community), `custom` (only when `documentsMode === 'all'`).
- **Sections → blocks**: embedded in the document. Each **block** has stable `id`, `officialContent`, optional voting anchor `currentWaveStartedAt`, edit metadata (`officialContentReason`: `initial` | `vote` | `admin`).
- **Variant** (`document_block_variants`): proposed alternative text for one block; `status`: `open` → `closed-winner` / `closed-not-winner` → optional `applied`; `withdrawn` if author retracts.
- **Votes**: reuse **`Vote`** with **`targetType === 'document-variant'`** and `targetId` = variant id (same quota/wallet/community rules as other weighted votes; Future Vision may require comment text — see `votes.router` / @business-future-vision.mdc).

---

## Community settings (documents hub)

- **`Community.settings.documentsMode`**: `'off'` | `'visionOrDescriptionOnly'` | `'all'` — controls whether only seeded OB/description docs exist vs arbitrary custom documents.
- **`documentCreators`**, **`documentVariantCost`**, **`documentVotingDurationHours`**, **`documentDefaultMode`**, **`documentAutoApplyTimerHours`** — economy and defaults for variants/waves (see `community.schema` / shared-types).

---

## Apply modes (`MeriterDocument.mode`)

| Mode | Behaviour |
|------|-------------|
| **`manual`** | After a wave closes, a **`closed-winner`** variant must be **applied** by author/admin via **`documentVariants.applyVotingWinner`** (or **applyOpenAsAdmin** for override). |
| **`auto`** | After **`finalizeExpiredWaveOnBlock`**, if there is a **`closed-winner`** with **positive rating**, **`applyVariantToOfficial`** runs automatically with synthetic actor **`MERITER_DOCUMENT_AUTO_APPLY_USER_ID`** (`meriter-actors.constant.ts`). |

Manual UI apply is rejected when `mode !== 'manual'` for **`applyVotingWinner`**.

---

## Voting waves and cron

- **Wave open**: while **`DocumentVariantService`/document helpers** consider the block’s voting window open (`currentWaveStartedAt` + `votingDurationHours`), finalize does nothing.
- **Finalize**: **`finalizeExpiredWaveOnBlock(documentId, blockId)`** — ranks open variants by rating (tie-break `proposedAt`), assigns `closed-winner` / `closed-not-winner`, clears wave anchor; then **`tryAutoApplyWinner`** if `mode === 'auto'`.
- **Periodic sweep**: **`DocumentWaveCronService`** (`*/5 * * * *`) calls **`runPeriodicWaveSweep()`** — discovers `(documentId, blockId)` pairs with **`open`** variants, skips blocks still voting, otherwise **`finalizeExpiredWaveOnBlock`**.
- **Trigger on propose**: proposing a variant also calls **`finalizeExpiredWaveOnBlock`** first so elapsed waves close before a new open variant is added.

---

## Economics

- **Propose variant**: fee via **`document_variant_proposal`** (quota/wallet rules in **`DocumentVariantService`**); aligns with global burn for fees (see @business-merits.mdc / fees).
- **Max variant body length**: **5000** characters (API trim); rich HTML from WYSIWYG counts toward the limit.

---

## Mirror to legacy community fields (§5.3)

- OB (`type === 'imageOfFuture'`) and project description (`type === 'description'`): **`mirrorOfficialTextToCommunityIfApplicable`** updates **`futureVisionText`** / **`description`** on **`Community`**.
- **`concatOfficialPlainText`** builds plain text from block **`officialContent`**; **HTML is stripped** for mirror (**`stripHtmlForMirror`**) so legacy fields stay readable plain text while the document stores rich content.

